		<b>Comment By Betty, 1-04-06</b>
		<p>i went to a mall crawl being 16 or maybe a little older, and it was very scarey.  People start a pushing line, forcing the entire mob of people to be shoved back and forth.  Because of this i was pushed down a trampled resulting in a broken rib, with no one able to hear my plea for help.  I would never return.  I am so glad they no longer have this event.</p>
		
		<b>Comment By Michele M, 6-04-07</b>
		<p>I went to the mall crawl when I was a teen in '84-'86 with my friends .  I agree with Betty it was scarry but also very exciting fun to see the costumes and attend the revelry.  Now I take my own daughter to the Munchkin Masquerade which has been a blast. <br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
Enjoy Michele</p>
		
